State files an Amended Information charging battery (DVO), contrary to Section 940.19(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   Motion granted.   
No contest plea to the amended charge.   Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Domestic violense assessment and counseling;
2) Pay restitution of $3,986.89 to the victim; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Have no contact with the victim, Linda Louison, defendant must maintain a distance of 500 feet away from the victim.  Defendant must move away within the next 45 days from his current residence.  Exceptions to the no contact are if the victim comes toward him; contact in court for divorce proceedings; and incidental contact.  
6) Spend five (5) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 08-11-15 at 5:00 p.m.;
7) Pay costs of action;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined;
9) Attend batterer's treatment group.  
Exhibit 1, 7 photographs of the victim.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.
